comment_regular_data.body:
Hi, I've noticed that a few event-data types are missing/not detailed here, and I myself have an implementation: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/compare/master...Willaaaaaaa:neovim:patch-0325. Hopefully, this would help.

The reason why I haven't opened a PR yet is that I'm thinking whether we can achieve automatic type inference without manual annotations (like `---@cast`). Currently, our approaches require users to explicitly specify the type to get LSP support for `ev.data`.

@justinmk Do you think we should aim for "zero-annotation" (perhaps via `---@overload`, `---@generic`_[Generics are still WIP](https://github.com/LuaLS/lua-language-server/issues/1861)_ or something else, I've tried to do so but with no luck yet, do you have some ideas?) or should we provide these classes first?
